On Fri, 11 Aug 2006, Yves Goergen wrote:
> I can't apply the patch, the patch command asks me for the files and
> says it cannot find the header of a unified diff. Can anybody tell me
> how to use this patch? Usually, it works but not this time.

You just have to remove the first lines of the file. The first line should
be the one starting with "diff -u". You can use an ordinary text editor but 
make shure that no automatic line breaking or justification is done.

